Project

Summary

SoundFi is a simple DeFi app where users can deposit tokens to earn yield or borrow tokens by locking collateral.
It’s meant to test how lending and borrowing can run smoothly on the Soundness Layer testnet, while also exploring how zk-features can make the system safer and more transparent.

Name & Category

Project: SoundFi

Category: defi


Description

Most lending protocols are either too complex or not friendly for new users.
SoundFi tries to keep things simple:

Lenders put tokens in and earn interest.

Borrowers lock collateral and get liquidity.

If collateral value drops, the system handles liquidation.


This is mainly an experiment to show how Soundness Layer can support basic DeFi primitives.

SL Integration

Contracts deployed directly on SL testnet.

Using SL RPC for transactions & wallet connection.

Plan to test zk-verification for loan health checks in the future.



